  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want my password to be protected so that no one can steal it.\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I want sensitive data to be removed from app-db as soon as possible so that I can't accidentally leak it.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: After account creation, data under the `:accounts/create` key stays there, containing `:password` and `:password-confirm`.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nSensitive data gets removed from DB when it is no longer needed.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nSensitive data stays in DB.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- install handler or interceptor that logs `(:accounts/create db)`\r\n- Open Status\r\n- trigger handler\r\n- observe `adb logcat`\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n*Summary*: Remove the passwords after completing account creation.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: latest code on `develop` branch\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\nThis log was produced using a custom interceptor.\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (if on Android please replicate bug whilst running adb logcat)\r\n```\r\n04-04 20:13:09.225  5915  5999 I ReactNativeJS: INFO [status-im.utils.handlers:96] - Track interceptor {:step :enter-name, :password \"thepassword\", :password-confirm \"thepassword\", :error nil, :name \"mtest\", :show-welcome? true}\r\n```",
